  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "DOCUMENT CONTROLLER",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>JOB REQUIREMENT</strong></u></p><p>Responsible for overall project document control and management as per company or project specific procedure. Custodian of all incoming & outgoing official transmittals and responsible for IDC process within team.</p><p>Responsible for allocation of document number to documents, maintain traceability of revision history and of their logging into Company document management system from the bid phase till project completion.</p><p>Responsible for management of incoming documents, logging, filing, document management and internal distribution (as applicable)</p><p>Responsible for management of document transmission to external parties, including preparation of transmittal, logging, filing and document management (letters, faxes, etc.).</p><p>Promote and enforce use of standard templates and formats for proper document preparation, distribution & storage. Responsible for data management including upload, report generation etc. in Windchill program. Periodic review of Windchill system for suggesting improvements and assist in system maintenance with assistance from IT department.</p><p>Responsible for miscellaneous document control activities like copying, formatting, scanning, document binding, generation of folders spine, control of records/standards/specification in Library etc.</p><p>Perform other duties as required and advised by General Manager, Head of Projects & Engineering.<br /></p><p><u><strong>QUALIFICATION REQUIREMENT</strong></u><br />Degree/Diploma in computer Science</p><p></p><p><u><strong>EXPERIENCE REQUIREMENT</strong></u></p><p>5 years of experience in document control, preferably in the Oil & Gas Industry. Basic IT competency in Microsoft Office suite, E-mail</p>",
